How to set this up on a fresh Ubuntu VM
Install Docker & Docker Compose:
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y docker.io docker-compose
sudo systemctl enable --now docker
Create config folders:
mkdir -p ~/appdata/radarr ~/appdata/sonarr ~/appdata/sabnzbd \
         ~/appdata/prowlarr ~/appdata/bazarr
Ensure media folders exist and have correct permissions:
mkdir -p /mnt/storage/downloads /mnt/storage/movies /mnt/storage/tv
sudo chown -R craig:craig ~/appdata /mnt/storage
sudo chmod -R 775 ~/appdata /mnt/storage
Copy this docker-compose.yaml into ~/stack-media/compose.yaml:
mkdir -p ~/stack-media
nano ~/stack-media/compose.yaml  # paste the YAML content

Start the stack:
cd ~/stack-media
docker-compose up -d
docker ps
docker-compose logs -f
